http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/kozhikode/Chandy-to-hold-discussion/article14025535.ece

: Chief Minister Oommen Chandy will hold a discussion with the citizens of Kozhikode at the Malabar Palace here from 6 p.m. to 8 p.m. on Sunday as part of preparing the election manifesto of the Congress-led UDF for the Assembly polls.Trade union leaders, businessmen, social, cultural and religious leaders would take part in the meeting, UDF district committee chairman P. Sankaran, DCC president K.C. Abu told newspersons.Mr. Chandy would tour every district to elicit the views of the people. Several projects in the city, including the widening of the Mananchira-Vellimadukunnu road, were pending. All this would be discussed at the meeting, they said.